docs.lead_paragraph: The good-natured looking ticket puncher at one of the gates in a Grand Central Station waiting room was temporarily idle the other afternoon, when a questioner accosted him: "Will it be this door or the other for the 3:45 train?" "Both," replied the man, and then, with a reminiscent smile that detained his questioner, he added: "I suppose I should say eyther.
